{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Those of us who believe in heaven have some sort of idea of what heaven would be."},{"time":4000,"text":"And in my idea, heaven is satisfied curiosity."},{"time":7000,"text":"I think of heaven as a really comfortable cloud"},{"time":10000,"text":"where I can just lie down with my belly down,"},{"time":12000,"text":"like I was watching TV when I was a child, and my elbows up."},{"time":16000,"text":"And I can basically look everywhere I want,"},{"time":19000,"text":"see every movie I've always wanted to see."},{"time":21000,"text":"And in the same kind of trance that you can feel sometimes"},{"time":25000,"text":"in the subway in New York when you're reading,"},{"time":26000,"text":"there's something really soothing and easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"Well, the funny thing is that I already have that kind of life, in a way,"},{"time":32000,"text":"because I discovered ..."},{"time":35000,"text":"it took me a while to understand it,"},{"time":36000,"text":"but when I discovered around 24 years of age that I was much more comfortable"},{"time":41000,"text":"with objects than with people, I finally decided to really embrace this passion."},{"time":47000,"text":"And I basically live my life in sort of a trance,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and I look around and everything I see is just the beginning of a long story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"Just to give you an example:"},{"time":56000,"text":"this is the exhibition, Humble Masterpieces, as it was at MoMA in 2004."},{"time":61000,"text":"We were in Queens,"},{"time":62000,"text":"we were building the big, big, big, big building in Midtown,"},{"time":65000,"text":"so we were in the small, small, small boondocks."},{"time":67000,"text":"That was one of the funnest moments of my career."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"But it's not only that."},{"time":72000,"text":"The typeface -- the typeface is Helvetica;"},{"time":74000,"text":"it's its 50th anniversary this year."},{"time":77000,"text":"And so I start thinking -- Max Miedinger and all those Swiss designers together,"},{"time":81000,"text":"trying to outdo Akzidenz-Grotesk, and come up with a new sans-serif typeface --"},{"time":86000,"text":"and the movie starts playing in my head already."},{"time":89000,"text":"And of course, you can imagine, with Humble Masterpieces"},{"time":92000,"text":"it was the same thing multiplied by a hundred."},{"time":95000,"text":"And I do hope, by the way, that the real goal of the exhibition"},{"time":98000,"text":"is going to have the same effect on you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"The exhibition was meant to be a way to have children think of doing ..."},{"time":106000,"text":"you know when they do homeworks at home?"},{"time":108000,"text":"Instead of having a tray with two peas, I was hoping that they would go"},{"time":111000,"text":"into the kitchen cabinet or the mother's handbag"},{"time":114000,"text":"and do their museum-quality design collection on a tray."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"So, everybody's always suggesting new humble masterpieces,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and at MoMA we put out some books"},{"time":123000,"text":"just for people to suggest their own humble masterpieces."},{"time":127000,"text":"And when you do that, usually you get 80 percent porn and 20 percent real suggestions,"},{"time":132000,"text":"and instead it was all -- almost -- all good suggestions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137000,"text":"And a lot of nationalism came in."},{"time":139000,"text":"For instance, I didn't know that the Spaniards invented the mop,"},{"time":143000,"text":"but they were very proud"},{"time":144000,"text":"so every Spaniard said \"la frego.\" And Italians did the pizza."},{"time":147000,"text":"And I wanted to show you, also, the suggestions from Kentucky are pretty good --"},{"time":151000,"text":"they had moonshine, laundry detergents and liquid nails."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"And I keep it going, and I just got,"},{"time":155000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":156000,"text":"also, this suggestion from Milan:"},{"time":159000,"text":"it's our traffic divider, which we call \"panettone,\" and it's painted;"},{"time":164000,"text":"it's these beautiful concrete things that you use around Milan"},{"time":168000,"text":"to define all the lanes of traffic."},{"time":170000,"text":"So, think of your own,"},{"time":171000,"text":"send them on if you want to -- they're always welcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"But an exhibition like that made me understand even more"},{"time":179000,"text":"what I've been thinking of for 13 years ever since I got to MoMA."},{"time":183000,"text":"I'm Italian. In Italy, design is normal."},{"time":186000,"text":"Different parts of the world have a knack for different things."},{"time":190000,"text":"I was just recently in Argentina and in Uruguay,"},{"time":194000,"text":"and the default way of building homes in the country is a beautiful modernism"},{"time":200000,"text":"that you don't see elsewhere, but the contemporary art was terrible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"In Italy, in Milan especially,"},{"time":206000,"text":"contemporary art really doesn't have that much of a place."},{"time":210000,"text":"But design -- oh, my God."},{"time":211000,"text":"What you find at the store at the corner, without going to any kind of fancy store,"},{"time":216000,"text":"is the kind of refined design that makes everybody think that"},{"time":218000,"text":"we are all so sophisticated."},{"time":220000,"text":"It's just what you find at the store."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"And New York has another kind of knack for contemporary art."},{"time":227000,"text":"I'm always amazed -- three-year-olds know who Richard Serra is"},{"time":232000,"text":"and take you to the galleries."},{"time":234000,"text":"But design, for some reason, is still misunderstood for decoration."},{"time":238000,"text":"It's really interesting:"},{"time":240000,"text":"what many people think when I say the word \"design\" is they think of"},{"time":244000,"text":"this kind of overdesigned -- in this case, it's overdesigned on purpose, but --"},{"time":249000,"text":"decoration, interior decoration."},{"time":251000,"text":"They think of somebody choosing fabrics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"Design can be that, of course, but it can also be this."},{"time":257000,"text":"It can be a school of design in Jerusalem that tries to find a better way"},{"time":262000,"text":"to design gas masks for people,"},{"time":263000,"text":"because, as you know, Israel deploys one gas mask per person including babies."},{"time":269000,"text":"So, what these designers do is they find a way to lower the neckline,"},{"time":274000,"text":"so that instead of being completely strangled, a teenager can also sip a Coke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"They tried to make a toddler's gas mask in such a way that the toddler"},{"time":286000,"text":"can be held by the parent because proximity of the body is so important."},{"time":291000,"text":"And then they make a little tent for the baby."},{"time":292000,"text":"However cruel, however ruthless you can think this is it's a great design,"},{"time":298000,"text":"and it is miles away from the fancy furniture,"},{"time":302000,"text":"but still, it's part of my same field of passion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"What I've been doing at MoMA since the beginning is to try to"},{"time":310000,"text":"harness the power of MoMA"},{"time":312000,"text":"because it's great to work there. You really have power"},{"time":315000,"text":"in that people usually tend to know about your exhibition or see the exhibitions,"},{"time":320000,"text":"and that is power because in a design museum I wouldn't have as many visitors."},{"time":325000,"text":"I'm very well aware that 80 percent of my public is there to see Picasso and Matisse,"},{"time":330000,"text":"and then they stumble upon my show and I keep them there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333000,"text":"But what I've been trying to do is something that the curators at MoMA"},{"time":336000,"text":"in my department have been doing ever since the museum was founded in 1929,"},{"time":340000,"text":"which is to try and see what's going on in the world"},{"time":343000,"text":"and try to use that authority in order to make things better."},{"time":347000,"text":"There have been many episodes,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and actually Eames Demetrius may be here in the audience,"},{"time":352000,"text":"but in two instances, his great-grandfather, grandfather --"},{"time":357000,"text":"I'm always a little perplexed about the relation, exactly --"},{"time":362000,"text":"Charles Eames the first time and then Charles and Ray Eames the second time"},{"time":366000,"text":"were involved in two competitions:"},{"time":368000,"text":"one in 1940, it was about organic furniture, and the second one in 1948"},{"time":373000,"text":"was low-cost furniture for the GIs coming back from the war"},{"time":377000,"text":"that then sparked a whole line of furniture."},{"time":380000,"text":"And then there was good design for very low price."},{"time":385000,"text":"There were a lot of programs in architecture and design that were about"},{"time":389000,"text":"pointing people in the direction of a better design for a better life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"So, I started out in '95 with this exhibition that was called"},{"time":398000,"text":"Mutant Materials in Contemporary Design."},{"time":400000,"text":"It was about a new phase, in my opinion, in the world of design"},{"time":404000,"text":"in that materials could be customized by the designers themselves."},{"time":408000,"text":"And that put me in touch with such diverse design examples as the aerogels"},{"time":416000,"text":"from the Lawrence Livermore Lab in California;"},{"time":418000,"text":"at that time, they were beginning to be brought into the civilian market."},{"time":424000,"text":"And at the same time, the gorgeous work of Takeshi Ishiguro, who did these"},{"time":427000,"text":"beautiful salt-and-pepper containers that are made of rice dough."},{"time":431000,"text":"So you see, the range is really quite diverse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"And then, for instance, this other exhibition"},{"time":438000,"text":"that was entitled Workspheres in 2001,"},{"time":442000,"text":"where I asked different designers to come up with ideas for"},{"time":446000,"text":"the new type of work styles that were happening in the world at that time."},{"time":451000,"text":"And you see IDEO there."},{"time":453000,"text":"It was beautiful -- it was called Personal Skies."},{"time":456000,"text":"The idea was that if you had a cubicle, you could project a sky on top"},{"time":460000,"text":"of your head and have your own \"Cielo in Una Stanza\" -- a sky in a room --"},{"time":464000,"text":"it's a very famous Italian song."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466000,"text":"And other examples: this was Marti Guixe about working on the go,"},{"time":470000,"text":"and Hella Jongerius, my favorite, about how to work at home."},{"time":473000,"text":"And this lets me introduce a very important idea about design:"},{"time":478000,"text":"designers are the biggest synthesizers in the world."},{"time":481000,"text":"What they do best is make a synthesis of human needs,"},{"time":486000,"text":"current conditions in economy, in materials, in sustainability issues,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and then what they do at the end -- if they are good --"},{"time":494000,"text":"is much more than the sum of its parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"Hella Jongerius is a person that is able to make a synthesis"},{"time":499000,"text":"that is really quite amazing"},{"time":502000,"text":"and also quite hilarious."},{"time":503000,"text":"The idea behind her work was that"},{"time":506000,"text":"at that time, everybody was saying you have to really divide your life."},{"time":510000,"text":"Instead, she said, \"No, no. Work and leisure can be together.\""},{"time":513000,"text":"Yeah, that's particularly gorgeous -- it's the TV dinner of 2001."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"There have been many other exhibitions in the meantime,"},{"time":521000,"text":"but I don't want to focus on my shows."},{"time":522000,"text":"I would like, instead, to talk about how great some designers are."},{"time":526000,"text":"I've always had a hard time with the word \"maverick.\""},{"time":528000,"text":"I came to the United States 13 years ago, and to this day"},{"time":530000,"text":"I have to ask, \"What does that mean?\""},{"time":533000,"text":"So, this morning I went to see on the dictionary and it said that"},{"time":536000,"text":"there was this gentleman that was not branding its cattle."},{"time":539000,"text":"Therefore, he was not following everybody's lead,"},{"time":542000,"text":"and therefore, he was a maverick."},{"time":543000,"text":"So, designers do need to be mavericks,"},{"time":547000,"text":"because the best way to design a successful object --"},{"time":550000,"text":"and also an object that we were missing before --"},{"time":554000,"text":"is to pretend that either it never existed"},{"time":557000,"text":"or that people will be able to have a new behavior with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"So, Safe is the last exhibition that I did at MoMA"},{"time":565000,"text":"and it ended at the beginning of last year."},{"time":568000,"text":"It was about design that deals with safety and deals with protection."},{"time":571000,"text":"It's a long story because it started before 2001 and it was called Emergency."},{"time":576000,"text":"And then when 9/11 happened, I had a shock and I canceled the exhibition"},{"time":582000,"text":"until, slowly but surely, it came back --"},{"time":585000,"text":"as a half-full glass instead of half-empty --"},{"time":588000,"text":"and it was about protection and safety."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"But it ranged from such items as a complete de-mining equipment to"},{"time":597000,"text":"these kind of water-sterilizing straws,"},{"time":601000,"text":"so it was really wide-ranging."},{"time":602000,"text":"It also had ... you know, Cameron and I worked a little bit together,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and some of the entries that you see in his website were actually in the exhibition."},{"time":610000,"text":"But what is interesting is that we don't need to talk about design and art anymore;"},{"time":617000,"text":"design uses whatever tools it has at its disposal in order to make a point."},{"time":621000,"text":"It's a sense of economy and a sense, also, of humor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"This is a beautiful project by Ralph Borland, who's South African."},{"time":628000,"text":"It's a suit for civil disobedience."},{"time":630000,"text":"The idea is that when you have a riot or a protest"},{"time":633000,"text":"and the police comes towards you, you're wearing this thing --"},{"time":636000,"text":"it's like a big heart and it has a loudspeaker over your heart"},{"time":640000,"text":"so your heartbeat is amplified --"},{"time":641000,"text":"and the police is reminded;"},{"time":643000,"text":"it's like having a flower in front of the rifle."},{"time":646000,"text":"And also, you can imagine, a whole group of people with the same suit"},{"time":651000,"text":"will have this mounting collective heartbeat that will be scary to the police."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"So, designers sometimes don't do things that are immediately"},{"time":658000,"text":"functional, but they're functional to our understanding of issues."},{"time":662000,"text":"Tony Dunne and Fiona Raby"},{"time":664000,"text":"did this series of objects that are about our anguish and our paranoia,"},{"time":670000,"text":"like this hideaway furniture that's made in the same wood as your floor"},{"time":674000,"text":"so it disappears completely and you can hide away;"},{"time":676000,"text":"or even better, the huggable atomic mushroom, which got me an article"},{"time":681000,"text":"on the Bulletin of Atomic Scientists of the United States --"},{"time":684000,"text":"I don't think it ever happened before at MoMA;"},{"time":686000,"text":"or this Faraday Chair that is supposed to protect you from radiations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689000,"text":"But the interesting thing in the exhibition is the discovery that"},{"time":695000,"text":"the ultimate shelter is your sense of self,"},{"time":697000,"text":"and there are quite a few designers that are working on this particular topic."},{"time":702000,"text":"This is Cindy van den Bremen, who is a Dutch designer"},{"time":704000,"text":"that's done this series of Capsters."},{"time":706000,"text":"They are athletic gear for Muslim women that enable them to ski, play tennis,"},{"time":713000,"text":"do whatever they want to do without having to uncap themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717000,"text":"And sometimes by doing this kind of research,"},{"time":721000,"text":"you encounter such beautiful ideas of design."},{"time":723000,"text":"Twan Verdonck is really young, I think he's 27, and working together with"},{"time":729000,"text":"some psychologist he did a series of toys that are for sensorial"},{"time":733000,"text":"stimulation for children that have psychological impairments."},{"time":735000,"text":"They're quite beautiful."},{"time":737000,"text":"They range from this fluffy toy that is about hugging you --"},{"time":740000,"text":"because autistic children like to be hugged tight, so it has a spring inside --"},{"time":744000,"text":"all the way to this doll with a mirror so the child can see him or herself"},{"time":749000,"text":"in the mirror and regain a sense of self."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753000,"text":"Design really looks upon the whole world"},{"time":756000,"text":"and it considers the world in all of its different ranges."},{"time":759000,"text":"I was recently at a conference on luxury organized by the Herald Tribune in Istanbul."},{"time":764000,"text":"And it was really interesting because I was the last speaker"},{"time":767000,"text":"and before me there were people that were really talking about luxury,"},{"time":770000,"text":"and I didn't want to be a party pooper but at the same time"},{"time":774000,"text":"I felt that I had to kind of bring back the discourse to reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776000,"text":"And the truth is that there are very different kinds of luxury,"},{"time":782000,"text":"and there's luxury that is relative for people that don't have that much."},{"time":786000,"text":"I want to make this point by showing you two examples of"},{"time":791000,"text":"design coming from a sense of economy -- very, very clear limits."},{"time":796000,"text":"This is Cuba, and this is the recycling of a squeaky toy as a bicycle bell,"},{"time":802000,"text":"and this is a raincoat that is made out of rice sacks."},{"time":807000,"text":"So they're quite beautiful, but they're beautiful because"},{"time":809000,"text":"they're so smart and economical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"And here is the work of two brothers from Sao Paulo,"},{"time":815000,"text":"Fernando and Humberto Campana, who got inspired by the poverty and"},{"time":821000,"text":"smartness that they saw around them to do pieces of furniture that now are"},{"time":825000,"text":"selling for an enormous amount of money."},{"time":827000,"text":"But that's because of the kind of strangeness of the market itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"So really, design takes everything into account,"},{"time":835000,"text":"and the interesting thing is that as the technology advances,"},{"time":838000,"text":"as we become more and more wireless and impalpable,"},{"time":842000,"text":"designers, instead, want us to be hands-on."},{"time":845000,"text":"Sometimes hammer-on."},{"time":846000,"text":"This is a whole series of furniture that wants to engage you physically."},{"time":851000,"text":"Even this chair that you have to open up and then sit on so that it takes"},{"time":855000,"text":"your imprint, all the way to this beautiful series of objects"},{"time":860000,"text":"that are considered design by Ana Mir in Barcelona."},{"time":863000,"text":"From this kind of bijou made with human hair to these chocolate nipples"},{"time":868000,"text":"to these intra-toe candies that your lover is supposed to suck from your toes."},{"time":872000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":873000,"text":"It's quite beautiful because somehow, this is a gorgeous moment for design."},{"time":878000,"text":"Many years ago I heard a mathematician from Vienna, whose name was Marchetti,"},{"time":885000,"text":"explain how the innovation in the military industry --"},{"time":889000,"text":"therefore, secret innovation -- and the innovation in the"},{"time":893000,"text":"civilian society are two sinusoids that are kind of opposed."},{"time":896000,"text":"And that makes sense."},{"time":898000,"text":"In moments of war there's great technological innovation,"},{"time":900000,"text":"and in the world you have to do without --"},{"time":903000,"text":"well, during the Second World War, you had to do without steel,"},{"time":905000,"text":"you had to do without aluminum."},{"time":906000,"text":"And then as peace comes, all of these technologies get all of a sudden"},{"time":911000,"text":"available for the civilian market."},{"time":913000,"text":"Many of you might know that the Potato Chip Chair"},{"time":916000,"text":"by Charles and Ray Eames comes exactly from that kind of instance:"},{"time":920000,"text":"fiberglass was available for civilian use all of a sudden."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923000,"text":"I think that this is a strange moment."},{"time":926000,"text":"The rhythm of the sinusoids has changed tremendously,"},{"time":928000,"text":"just like the rhythm of our life in the past 25 years,"},{"time":932000,"text":"so I'm not sure anymore what the wavelength is."},{"time":935000,"text":"But it surely is a very important moment for design,"},{"time":939000,"text":"because not only is the technology proceeding, not only is computing"},{"time":943000,"text":"technology making open-source possible also in the world of design,"},{"time":948000,"text":"but also the idea of sustainability --"},{"time":950000,"text":"which is not only sustainability from the viewpoint of CO2 emissions and footprint,"},{"time":956000,"text":"but also sustainability of human interrelationships --"},{"time":959000,"text":"is very much part of the work of so many designers."},{"time":962000,"text":"And that's why designers, more and more, are working on behaviors"},{"time":965000,"text":"rather than on objects."},{"time":966000,"text":"Especially the good ones, not all of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":969000,"text":"I wanted to show you, for instance, the work of Mathieu Lehanneur,"},{"time":973000,"text":"which is quite fantastic."},{"time":974000,"text":"He's another young designer from France who's working --"},{"time":977000,"text":"and at this point he's working, also, with pharmaceutical companies --"},{"time":979000,"text":"on new ways to engage patients, especially children,"},{"time":983000,"text":"in taking their medicines with constancy and with certainty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"For instance, this is a beautiful container for asthma medicine"},{"time":991000,"text":"that kind of inflates itself when it's time for you to take the medicine,"},{"time":994000,"text":"so the child has to go -- pffff! -- to release and relieve the container itself."},{"time":999000,"text":"And this other medicine is something that you can draw on your skin,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"so intradermal delivery enables you to joyfully be involved"},{"time":1007000,"text":"in this particular kind of delivery."},{"time":1009000,"text":"Similarly, there's the work of people like Marti Guixe that tries to involve"},{"time":1015000,"text":"you in a way that is really about making everything pass through your mouth"},{"time":1020000,"text":"so that you learn from your mistakes or from your taste, orally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027000,"text":"The next show that I'm going to work on --"},{"time":1029000,"text":"and I've been bugging a lot of you about this here --"},{"time":1032000,"text":"is about the relationship between design and science."},{"time":1034000,"text":"I'm trying to find not the metaphors, but, rather, the points in common --"},{"time":1038000,"text":"the common gripes, the common issues, the common preoccupations --"},{"time":1042000,"text":"and I think that it will enable us to go a little further in this idea of design"},{"time":1049000,"text":"as an instruction, as a direction rather than a prescription of form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"And I am hoping that many of you will respond to this."},{"time":1058000,"text":"I've sent an email already to quite a few of you."},{"time":1061000,"text":"But design and science and the possibility of visualizing different scales,"},{"time":1065000,"text":"and therefore, really work at the scale of the very small"},{"time":1069000,"text":"to make it very big and very meaningful."},{"time":1071000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}